text: Emma Maud Valborg Larsson (born 15 November 1998) is a Swedish female former artistic gymnast and a member of the national team. Larsson participated at the 2015 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships in Glasgow. She was seen as a very talented gymnast for her age.Emma Larsson tittar framåt – trots finalmiss She eventually qualified for 2016 Summer Olympics, where she placed thirty- fifth in the qualifying stage of the competition with a total score of 54.332. Shortly after the Summer Olympics, she suffered a meniscus tear and was forced to undergo knee surgery with a long rehabilitation period. She could not participate at the 2017 World Championships. Due to many setbacks she had, she lost motivation and retired from gymnastics in December 2017 at the age of 19 years old.19-åriga OS-gymnasten slutar ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Swedish gymnasts
